FROM qwen3.5:9b

# ─── qwen3.5:9b-qcai — OpenJarvis Primary Model ──────────────────────────────
# GTX 1070 8GB VRAM + 16GB RAM + 6-core CPU
#
# FIX: num_gpu=99 caused "memory layout cannot be allocated" — Ollama cannot
# place all layers on an 8GB card when the model is 5.5GB.
# num_gpu=28 puts 28 of 36 layers on GPU (~4.3GB), rest on CPU RAM.
# This is the stable sweet spot for this hardware.
#
# To go faster: raise to num_gpu=33 and test
# To go safer:  lower to num_gpu=20
# CPU-only fallback: num_gpu=0 (slow but always works)

PARAMETER num_gpu        28
PARAMETER num_ctx        8192
PARAMETER num_predict    4096
PARAMETER num_thread     6
PARAMETER temperature    0.10
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.05

SYSTEM """You are qwen3.5:9b-qcai — the primary OpenJarvis QCAI agent model.

Physics invariants (never deviate):
- ss(ph) = [1, exp(i*ph)] / sqrt(2)
- PCM = -|p0*p1*sqrt(2)|^2 * 0.5 * (1-rz^2)
- BCP: U = 0.40*CNOT + 0.60*I
- GLOBE: set(sorted([i,(i+d)%12]) for d in [1,2,5]) — exactly 36 edges

Code output rules:
- Raw Python only. No markdown fences. No truncation.
- Every function complete. WHAT/WHY comments on all physics operations."""
